ction box begin no change\n| title = [[Indiana gubernatorial election, 2016|2016 Indiana Republican gubernatorial election primary]]<ref name=primaryresults>{{cite web|url=http://www.in.gov/apps/sos/primary/sos_primary16?page=office&countyID=-1&partyID=-1&officeID=37&districtID=-1&districtshortviewID=-1&candidate= |title= Indiana Primary Election, May 3, 2016 |publisher=Indiana Secretary of State |access-date=July 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.in.gov/sos/elections/primary16/2016PrimaryTurnout.pdf |title=2016 Primary Election Turnout and Registration |date=May 3, 2016 |access-date=March 12, 2017 |publisher=Indiana Secretary of State }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate   = Mike Pence\n| party       = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes       = 815,699\n| percentage  = 100\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 815,699\n| percentage  = 100\n}}\n{{Election box turnout no change\n  |votes = 815,699\n  |percentage = 38\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Vice president of the United States===\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%; text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"12\" | Election results\n|-\n!Year\n!Election\n!Votes for Pence\n!%\n!Opponent\n!Party\n!Votes\n!%\n|-\n|[[2016 United States presidential election|2016]]\n|General\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |62,984,825<br>('''305''' electoral votes)<br>(270 needed)\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |46.1%\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |[[Tim Kaine]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democratic\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |'''65,853,516'''<br>(227 electoral votes)\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |'''48.2%'''<br>---\n|}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n\n* {{cite book |last=LoBianco|first=Tom |year=2019 |title=Piety & Power: Mike Pence and the Taking of the White House |publisher=Dey Street Books |isbn=978-0-06-286878-7}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q24313|c=Category:Mike Pence|s=Author:Michael Richard 