{"title_page": "List of people from New York City", "text_new": "{{short description|List of people from New York City, US}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2015}}\n[[File:NYC-Skyline-1.jpg|thumb|right|400px|alt=New York City Skyline|New York City]]\nMany notable [[people]] were either born or adopted in [[New York City]].\n{{TOC limit|limit=2}}\n\n== People from New York City ==\n\n{{dynamic list|date=October 2011}}\n{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}\n\n=== 0\u20139 ===\n*[[50 Cent]] (Curtis Jackson)&nbsp;\u2013 businessman and [[rapping|rapper]]\n*[[6ix9ine]] (Daniel Hernandez)&nbsp;\u2013 [[rapping|rapper]]\n\n=== A ===\n{{div col}}\n*[[Aaliyah]] (Aaliyah Haughton, 1979\u20132001)&nbsp;\u2013 singer, actress, model\n*[[Zaid Abdul-Aziz]] (born 1946)&nbsp;\u2013 professional basketball player\n*[[Kareem Abdul-Jabbar]] (born 1947)&nbsp;\u2013 basketball player\n*[[George Abernethy]] (1807\u20131877)\n{{spaced ndash}} first provisional [[Governor of Oregon]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\">{{cite book | title = Who Was Who in America, Historical Volume, 1607\u20131896 | publisher = Marquis Who's Who | location=Chicago | year = 1967}}</ref>\n*[[Cecile Abish]] (born 1930)&nbsp;\u2013 sculptor\n*[[Oday Aboushi]] (born 1991)&nbsp;\u2013 football player\n*[[Ray Abruzzo]] (born 1954)&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n*[[Garnett Adrain]] (1815\u20131878){{spaced ndash}} member of the [[United States House of Representatives]] from [[New Jersey]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[Cornelius Rea Agnew]] (1830\u20131888){{spaced ndash}} [[ophthalmologist]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[Eliza Agnew]] (1807\u20131883){{spaced ndash}} [[Presbyterian]] [[missionary]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[Christina Aguilera]] (born 1980)&nbsp;\u2013 singer\n*[[Danny Aiello]] (1933\u20132019)&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n*[[Marv Albert]] (born 1941)&nbsp;\u2013 sports announcer\n*[[Alan Alda]] (born 1936)&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n*[[Ira Aldridge]] (1805\u20131867){{spaced ndash}} stage actor<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[William Alexander, Lord Stirling]] (1726\u20131783){{spaced ndash}} [[major general]] in the [[American Revolutionary War]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[Nancy Allen (actress)|Nancy Allen]] (born 1950)&nbsp;\u2013 actress\n*[[Woody Allen]] (born 1935)&nbsp;\u2013 film director, actor, screenwriter\n*[[Vincent Alo]] (1904\u20132001)&nbsp;\u2013 mobster\n*[[Rafer Alston]]&nbsp;\u2013 basketball player\n*[[Lee J. Ames]]&nbsp;\u2013 illustrator and writer; known for the ''Draw 50...'' learn-to-draw books\n*[[Trey Anastasio]] (born 1964)&nbsp;\u2013 rock musician and member of the band, [[Phish]]\n*[[Kenny Anderson (basketball)|Kenny Anderson]]&nbsp;\u2013 professional basketball player\n*[[Natalie and Nadiya Anderson]] \u2013 twins, television personalities; contestants on ''[[The Amazing Race (U.S. TV series)|The Amazing Race]]'' and winner of ''[[Survivor: San Juan del Sur]]'\n*[[Charles Anthon]]{{spaced ndash}} classical scholar<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[Carmelo Anthony]]&nbsp;\u2013 basketball player\n*[[Marc Anthony]]&nbsp;\u2013 singer and actor\n*[[Judd Apatow]]&nbsp;\u2013 producer, director, comedian, actor and screenwriter\n*[[Fiona Apple]]&nbsp;\u2013 singer-songwriter\n*[[Jacob M. Appel|Jacob Appel]]&nbsp;\u2013 (born 1973), short story writer and bioethicist, born in New York City\n*[[Diane Arbus]] (1923\u20131971)&nbsp;\u2013 photographer\n*[[Nate Archibald]] (born 1948)&nbsp;\u2013 professional basketball player\n*[[Edward Arnold (actor)|Edward Arnold]] (1890\u20131956)&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n*[[Rosanna Arquette]] (born 1959)&nbsp;\u2013 actress\n*[[Kenneth J. Arrow]]&nbsp;\u2013 economist; recipient, 1972 [[Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences]]\n*[[Beatrice Arthur]] (1922\u20132009)&nbsp;\u2013 actress\n*[[William H. Aspinwall]]&nbsp;\u2013 railroad promoter<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[John Jacob Astor III]] (1822\u20131890)&nbsp;\u2013 businessman and member of the [[Astor family]]\n*[[Vincent Astor]] (1891\u20131959)&nbsp;\u2013 businessman, philanthropist and member of the [[Astor family]]\n*[[William Backhouse Astor, Sr.]] (1792\u20131875)&nbsp;\u2013 businessman and member of the [[Astor family]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\" />\n*[[Ren\u00e9 Auberjonois]] (1940\u20132019)&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n*[[Jake T. Austin]]&nbsp;\u2013 actor, model, author\n*[[Awkwafina]] (Nora Lum, born 1988)&nbsp;\u2013 rapper, actress\n*[[AZ (rapper)|AZ]] &nbsp;\u2013 rapper and former member of the rap group [[The Firm (hip hop group)|The Firm]]\n*[[Hank Azaria]] (born 1964)&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== B ===\n{{div col}}\n*[[Edwin Burr Babbitt]]&nbsp;\u2013 actor\n*[[Johnny Bach]] (1924\u20132016)&nbsp;\u2013 professional basketball player and coach\n*[[Evan Baken]]&nbsp;\u2013 musician, drummer and record company executive\n*[[William Bliss Baker]]&nbsp;\u2013 landscape artist\n*[[Azealia Banks]] (born 1991)&nbsp;\u2013 rapper, singer-songwriter, actress\n*[[Lloyd Banks]] (born 1982)&nbsp;\u2013 rapper\n*[[Joseph Barbera]] (1911\u20132006){{spaced ndash}} animator, producer, director, [[MGM]] and co-founder of [[Hanna-Barbera]]\n*[[Bryan Bautista]]&nbsp;\u2013 Dominican-American musician, singer, and contestant from [[NBC]]'s ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'' season 10\n*[[Earl Beecham]]&nbsp;\u2013 football player\n*[[Harry Belafonte]] (born 1927)&nbsp;\u2013 singer, songwriter, activist & actor\n*[[Bo Belinsky]] (1936\u20132001)&nbsp;\u2013 Major League Baseball player\n*[[Tony Bennett]]&nbsp;\u2013 jazz singer and musician\n*[[Lillie Berg]] (1845\u20131896)&nbsp;\u2013 musician, musical educator\n*[[Moe Berg]] (1902\u20131972) {{spaced ndash}} [[Major League Baseball]] player and spy\n*[[Milton Berle]]&nbsp;\u2013 comedian\n*[[Paul Berlenbach]] (1901\u20131985)&nbsp;\u2013 light heavyweight boxing champion, 1925\u20131926\n*[[Dellin Betances]]&nbsp;\u2013 Major League Baseball pitcher\n*[[Acid Betty]]&nbsp;\u2013 drag queen\n*[[Bipolar Explore